<Link id="l00448" /><CodeLine lineNumber="448"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Selects a new architecture by updating the FeatureBits with the necessary</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00449" /><CodeLine lineNumber="449"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// info including implied dependencies.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00450" /><CodeLine lineNumber="450"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Internally, it clears all the feature bits related to &#42;any&#42; architecture</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00451" /><CodeLine lineNumber="451"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// and selects the new one using the ToggleFeature functionality of the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00452" /><CodeLine lineNumber="452"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// MCSubtargetInfo object that handles implied dependencies. The reason we</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00453" /><CodeLine lineNumber="453"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// clear all the arch related bits manually is because ToggleFeature only</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00454" /><CodeLine lineNumber="454"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// clears the features that imply the feature being cleared and not the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00455" /><CodeLine lineNumber="455"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// features implied by the feature being cleared. This is easier to see</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00456" /><CodeLine lineNumber="456"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// with an example:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00457" /><CodeLine lineNumber="457"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  --------------------------------------------------</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00458" /><CodeLine lineNumber="458"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// | Feature         | Implies                        |</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00459" /><CodeLine lineNumber="459"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// | -------------------------------------------------|</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00460" /><CodeLine lineNumber="460"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// | FeatureMips1    | None                           |</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00461" /><CodeLine lineNumber="461"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// | FeatureMips2    | FeatureMips1                   |</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00462" /><CodeLine lineNumber="462"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// | FeatureMips3    | FeatureMips2 | FeatureMipsGP64 |</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00463" /><CodeLine lineNumber="463"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// | FeatureMips4    | FeatureMips3                   |</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00464" /><CodeLine lineNumber="464"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// | ...             |                                |</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00465" /><CodeLine lineNumber="465"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//  --------------------------------------------------</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00466" /><CodeLine lineNumber="466"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00467" /><CodeLine lineNumber="467"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Setting Mips3 is equivalent to set: (FeatureMips3 | FeatureMips2 |</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00468" /><CodeLine lineNumber="468"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// FeatureMipsGP64 | FeatureMips1)</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00469" /><CodeLine lineNumber="469"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Clearing Mips3 is equivalent to clear (FeatureMips3 | FeatureMips4).</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l04201" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4201"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// SLT fits well with 2 of our 4 pseudo-branches:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l04202" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4202"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   BLT, where $rs &lt; $rt, translates into &quot;slt $at, $rs, $rt&quot; and</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l04203" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4203"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//   BGT, where $rs &gt; $rt, translates into &quot;slt $at, $rt, $rs&quot;.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l04204" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4204"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// If the result of the SLT is 1, we branch, and if it&#39;s 0, we don&#39;t.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l04205" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4205"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// This is accomplished by using a BNEZ with the result of the SLT.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l04206" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4206"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l04207" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4207"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The other 2 pseudo-branches are opposites of the above 2 (BGE with BLT</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l04208" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4208"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// and BLE with BGT), so we change the BNEZ into a BEQZ.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l04209" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4209"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Because only BGE and BLE branch on equality, we can use the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l04210" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4210"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// AcceptsEquality variable to decide when to emit the BEQZ.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l04211" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4211"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Note that the order of the SLT arguments doesn&#39;t change between</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l04212" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4212"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// opposites.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l04214" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4214"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The same applies to the unsigned variants, except that SLTu is used</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l04215" /><CodeLine lineNumber="4215"><Highlight kind="normal">  </Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// instead of SLT.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
